The paper focuses on the use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for image classification, which is a core topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of pre-trained CNNs as generic feature extractors, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper explores the feature aspect of CNNs, which is a key area of research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of Random Forests and SVMs, which are popular machine learning algorithms (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of lower-layer features for classification, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) as well as computer vision.
